<h1>Name</h1>
<p>wrap_text -- Break a text string into an array of lines</p>
<h1>Synopsis</h1>
<p>array <b>wrap_text</b> ( string string, float width[, array param])</p>
<h1>Description</h1>
<p>This function takes a text string and breaks it into an array of
strings based on the width parameter. The resultant array is broken
on word boundries and paragraph bounderies (newlines). The resultant
array can be used to paint the string, line-by-line on the page.</p>
<p>When a single word is too long to fit on a line, a blank line is
returned where that word would have existed, and the remainer of the
string is processed as normal.</p>
<p>The param array is used to determine font and font size.
If omitted, 12pt Helvetica is assumed.</p>
<h1>Examples</h1>
<p>Breaks the string $data into an array of strings, none of which
will be greater than 200 PDF units wide when placed as 12 point
Helvetica.</p>
<pre>
$strings = $pdf->wrap_text($data, 200);
</pre>
